IRS Raises Mileage Reimbursement Rate for Vehicle Business Use

-- B y   A n d r e w   Z a j a c
-- 
2011-06-23T14:59:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-23/irs-raises-mileage-reimbursement-rate-for-vehicle-business-use.html
Higher fuel prices have prompted the
 Internal Revenue Service  to raise the reimbursement rate for
mileage incurred in business use to 55.5 cents, the agency
announced.  The IRS said today the change will take effect July 1. The
current reimbursement rate for vehicle use is 51 cents.
Reimbursement rates for vehicle mileage incurred as a medical or
moving expense will rise to 23.5 cents.  The mileage rate for vehicles used as a charitable
contribution will remain at 14 cents.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrew Zajac in Washington at 
 azajac@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mark Silva at 
 msilva34@bloomberg.net  